Product description

LIGE 1.43'' Smart watch with Flashlight

LIGE Men's Smartwatch - Bold Military Design

This LIGE 1.43’’ round smart watch boasts a unique military-inspired look, crafted from composite metal with a brushed metal finish for a rugged, scratch-resistant, and durable exterior. It features H7 high-strength explosion-proof glass with excellent airtightness, making the entire body dustproof and waterproof. Equipped with LIGE’s latest high-magnetic clasp band, it combines an outer leather layer with an inner silicone lining for a stylish look and a skin-friendly, waterproof, and sweat-resistant feel. Notably, the magnetic clasp allows for easy adjustment of the strap length, making it both fashionable and functional—an ideal choice for a men’s smartwatch!

  • 530mAh Large Battery: Enjoy 7-10 days of normal usage and up to 30 days of low-power standby.
  • Two Interchangeable Straps: Includes a leather magnetic strap and a silicone strap to match different styles effortlessly.
  • LED Flashlight: One-touch activation provides a reliable light source for outdoor exploration and emergencies.
  • 1.43’’ AOD Touchscreen: The low-power Always-On Display lets you check the time at any moment, making this smartwatch a practical, stylish choice.
  • Multifunctional Features:Calculator/Weather Forecast/Stopwatch/Timer/Alarm Clock/Bluetooth Music Control/Calling Feature/Message Notifications/120+ Sports Modes/24-Hour Heart Rate Monitoring/Exercise Reminders/Pedometer

530mAh Large-Capacity Battery & Magnetic Charging Cable

  • The smartwatch is equipped with a large 530mAh battery, providing up to 7 days of regular standby time with just 2 hours of charging. In low-power mode, the standby time can extend up to 15 days.
  • It comes with a magnetic charging cable that is compact and convenient to carry, making it easy to take along whether you’re on a business trip or traveling.

Convenient Communication Device - Bluetooth Calling & Message Notifications

Durable Men's Military Smartwatch with Built-in Speaker and Microphone

This rugged men's military smartwatch is equipped with a high-quality speaker and microphone for stable, smooth call quality. Paired with your smartphone via Bluetooth, you can directly dial, answer, and end calls on the smartwatch. It also supports AI voice assistants. Additionally, you can play music and media audio on the smartwatch.

*If you prefer not to play audio from your phone on the smartwatch, go to "Settings" or swipe right on the main screen to find the "Call" icon, tap it, and turn off "Media Audio."

Bluetooth Calling Features:

  • Digital Dial Pad
  • Add up to 100 frequently used contacts
  • Call History Browsing
  • One-Touch Dialing
  • SOS Emergency Contacts with One-Touch Dialing

Smart Message Notifications:The smartwatch supports receiving notifications from your phone and vibrates to alert you, ensuring you never miss important messages.

Supported Apps: WhatsApp, Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, Skype, WeChat, email, messaging, and many other social media platforms.

24-Hour Health Monitoring

Durable Men's Smartwatch with Built-in Biometric Sensor

This durable men's smartwatch features a biometric sensor on the back, designed to closely fit your skin and monitor health data. The smartwatch displays data in an easy-to-read format, giving you valuable insights into your health!

  • 24-Hour Heart Rate Monitoring: The smartwatch continuously monitors your heart rate 24/7, creating an hourly heart rate graph. You can set threshold values in the app, and the watch will alert you if your heart rate exceeds a certain level, helping you stay aware of your health.
  • Blood Pressure/Blood Oxygen Monitoring: Simply tap the function, and it will start measuring real-time data.
  • Smart Sleep Tracking: The watch intelligently tracks sleep duration and quality, distinguishing between deep and light sleep.

Note: Health data from the watch is for reference only and should not be used as a substitute for medical-grade measurements.

1.43’’ AOD HD Touchscreen - 466*466 Pixels

  • The men’s smartwatch features a 1.43’’ AMOLED touchscreen with a high resolution of 466*466 pixels and 5 levels of adjustable brightness. This provides an ultra-clear visual experience and smooth, precise control. The AMOLED display offers an always-on feature (showing the time in low-power mode), allowing you to view the time without needing to operate the watch.
  • On the right side is an LED flashlight: the latest upgraded flashlight feature adds convenience and functionality. Whether you’re outdoors adventuring, cycling, hiking, walking at night, or in an emergency, you can fearlessly face the dark with one-touch flashlight activation. The light has a reach of 6-10 meters.

Outdoor Sports Smartwatch

  • This military-style men’s smartwatch features over 120 sports modes, covering a wide range of activities such as indoor and outdoor exercises, fitness training, core workouts, and machine-based exercises, meeting all your workout needs.
  • The tactical smartwatch monitors exercise data in real-time, including workout duration, distance, calories burned, and heart rate, giving you a comprehensive view of your performance metrics during workouts.
  • With over 120 sport modes available, including cycling, hiking, walking, running, jump rope, skiing, basketball, badminton, weightlifting, elliptical, golf, climbing, tennis, and soccer, this watch is built to support all your athletic pursuits.

Smartwatch Q&A

What’s Included with the Smartwatch?

  • Smartwatch ×1//Magnetic Leather Strap ×1//Silicone Strap ×1//Charging Cable ×1

How to Connect the Smartwatch for Calling?

  1. Download the “FitCloudPro” app on your smartphone.
  2. Open the “FitCloudPro” app, go to the “Device” screen, and click “Add New Device.”
  3. Select “EF7” to establish a connection.
  4. Allow the smartwatch to access phone information, then enable the “Bluetooth Calling” and “Message Notifications” options in settings.

What If the Strap is Damaged or There’s a Quality Issue with the Watch?

  • Feel free to ASK us, and we’ll resolve your issue within 24 hours.

      Purchased (not a vine reviewer, I actually bought this) watch a week ago and it came well packaged.

      Comments (Pros and Cons)
      - The watch itself looks great and the watch bands are comfortable, I have a smaller wrist but still think the watch is fine with a large clear screen
      - customer service via whatsapp messaging was top notch, although they could not solve all my issues they were really great to work with
      - the monitors seem to work decently (have not cross checked with other medical monitoring devices)
      - sleep tracking mostly just tracks time in bed and detects when you're asleep (although I don't think this is that accurate), it does not provide data on sleep stages
      - pedometer seems to work fine, it tracks fewer steps than my iPhone13 however I couldn't tell you which is more accurate
      - flashlight feature is useful
      - camera feature will allow you to control the shutter (take the photo), however it does not show you the actual image view you're about to take if you need that
      - water resistance is stated as 5ATM and IP68, however in speaking to customer service and reading the manual it was noted to NOT take a shower and also to not press the buttons when in water as it could pull moisture through the seals
      - weather app - I can not get this to function properly. continues to show that I'm in a warm weather area (and the temp reading has not changed at all). Customer support could not figure this out - it could be an iOS connection issue
      - after tinkering I was able to get iMessages to show. The screen is large enough that it will display quite a bit of text. In order to reply via voice assistant you need to unlock your iPhone so it's probably easier to just use Siri. One of the options under push notifications in the app is "more reminders" and I think turning this on vs just SMS allowed iMessages to come though
      - WhatsApp works well, I didn't test any other apps - don't need that many alerts on my watch
      - one feature I wish my smart watch had was a calendar synch, this watch does not have that feature (was never listed)
      - Bluetooth calling was fine, speaker and mic seem to work well - tested this in a quiet area

      OVERALL
      - nice looking watch with easy to swap bands
      - customer service is fantastic although depending on where you live you may have to be up late to communicate with them
      - iOS compatibility seems to work well, Bluetooth to iPhone is good although I need to figure out how to stop media on phone from playing sound off the watch as a default
      - weather app doesn't work but i can live with that
      - battery life has been great so far

      - this is my first SmartWatch and I'm happy with it. I will likely pick up a more work friendly watch that would alert me of my upcoming meetings but other than that I'm quite satisfied. The few issues I had are pretty minor given the cost for this watch - it was less than $75 CAD with the cyber deals / coupon

      Improvements: A truer understanding of water resistance and a feature to show the lens view of the camera on the watch would make this an outstanding device, also a compass would be a nice add on as well if someone phone battery ever runs out

    • Eric
      4.0 out of 5 starsAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product
      Super heavy and thick; but with a strong light.
      Reviewed in Canada on October 19, 2024
      I’ve reviewed a similar watch to this one in the past and the models are nearly identical. The casing is just as massive and the weight is super heavy due to the metallic build. If you like beefy watches with an aggressive look, this one could be for you. In terms of the... See more
      I’ve reviewed a similar watch to this one in the past and the models are nearly identical. The casing is just as massive and the weight is super heavy due to the metallic build. If you like beefy watches with an aggressive look, this one could be for you. In terms of the strap, it’s the standard heavy duty rubberized silicone with close-set notches so you can really dial in the fit. Really good stuff for outdoor use. The upside with this model is that it has little metallic leaflets on either side of the casing to protect the strap attachment pins and curve the face down towards the wrist. A nice touch imo. The user interface is pretty standard, with 2 pages in the swipe-down quick menu, but no swipe-right ‘recently used’ menu like on some of the less expensive daily wear watches. Unfortunately, all but 1 of the 9 pre-loaded dial faces are dynamic (with moving animations) and pretty much cluttered to the point of being unusable. The app doesn’t help since I can’t get any of the dial faces in the library to load, but if you can, you can only store one more dial face, with no option to delete the unusable ones. That’s a major drawback imo. Fortunately, you don’t need the app the use the watch since you can set the date and time right on it; but if you want to set alarms, you’ll be out of luck. Of course, you can just download the app to get the dial face you want, add a couple of alarm times, then unpair it; but if you want to track your data, you’ll need it paired at all times. Not a fan of the app myself since it doesn’t seem to function well on my older Samsung phone, but you can fiddle around with it if you have a newer model. It gets updates every few months. Back to the watch, the flashlight is VERY good in terms of brightness, although there are no external buttons to turn it on. You need to access the quick menu and tap the icon each time you want to use it. There’s only one brightness level too, but believe me, it’s more than enough in a dark room to find stuff. I have another smart watch with an external button for the light, but it’s nowhere near as strong as this one. The forward-facing design is simply superior. In terms of screen resolution, it’s quite good and there are 5 brightness levels which is pretty standard. The 2 AOD clocks – digital and analog – are both good too, so you can always just use them instead of the standard dial face. The sensor on the back that uses light to measure heart rate, O2 Sat and blood pressure is quite decent, although it does take a good 30 seconds to get a good read. Par for the course. But the calculator has great sensitivity on the buttons and the timer and stopwatch are both perfect. No problems there. Really, the biggest drawbacks of this model are the massive casing, heavy weight and unusable pre-loaded dial faces. The app function really seems to depend on the phone – for some it works great, for others it doesn’t – but you can always just use the watch as a stand-alone if you want to, substituting the AOD clocks for the dial face. Oh yeah, and I forgot to mention that the stand-by battery life is excellent, like with most other beefy watches with big batteries. Just be aware that if you do choose to the use the AOD clocks on a regular basis, they take up significantly more battery life than just having the screen off on stand-by. Like, if you normally have 12 days of battery, the AODs will cut it down to 3-4. Yeah, THAT much. Everything else about the watch, from the onboard features, to the flashlight and strap are very good. Durability for outdoor use is excellent like I mentioned, and I’ve submerged it in water on more than one occasion and it holds up well. Charge time takes a little longer because of the bigger battery, but it’s not much more than my other smart watches. Overall, I can’t give it a perfect score, but if you like heavier aggressive watches, I think 4 is a fair rating. Hope that helps.
